124
00:10:00,260 --> 00:10:03,270
Hey, so what? Tell me!

125
00:10:03,270 --> 00:10:08,370
I don't know. I really don't know when I started to like you.

126
00:10:10,180 --> 00:10:15,370
You should just say that you liked me from the start, like it was fate. Why so shy?

127
00:10:17,010 --> 00:10:19,790
Where's my constellation?

128
00:10:19,790 --> 00:10:21,960
You can't see it right now.

129
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,250
Why?

130
00:10:23,250 --> 00:10:25,420
Because yours is an autumn constellation!

131
00:10:25,420 --> 00:10:28,640
It already lived its life? It's dead?

132
00:10:29,700 --> 00:10:32,660
No, no, it's not that.

133
00:10:32,660 --> 00:10:34,700
It's a constellation you can only see in autumn.

134
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:39,210
Yeah, but I was born in the spring. That's when my birthday is.

135
00:10:39,210 --> 00:10:40,710
What are you saying?

136
00:10:40,710 --> 00:10:42,290
Why?

137
00:10:43,290 --> 00:10:47,140
No, it's not like that. You can just see the constellation in the autumn.

138
00:10:47,140 --> 00:10:49,290
But, why?

139
00:10:50,860 --> 00:10:53,070
So this is a pojangmacha.

140
00:10:53,070 --> 00:10:55,460
Pork skin and some soju?

141
00:10:55,460 --> 00:10:58,500
What kind of meat restaurant owner eats at another meat restaurant?

142
00:10:59,180 --> 00:11:01,730
Ma'am, I'm here.

143
00:11:12,270 --> 00:11:14,160
What's wrong?

144
00:11:19,710 --> 00:11:21,920
Look over there without making it too obvious.

145
00:11:29,700 --> 00:11:33,500
The woman in front of him isn't my mom, right?

146
00:11:34,380 --> 00:11:36,530
I don't think so.

147
00:11:41,970 --> 00:11:45,030
I think I know who she is.

148
00:11:45,030 --> 00:11:48,250
[Seol Young Won Pottery]

149
00:11:48,250 --> 00:11:50,930
[Seol Young Won Pottery]
"Pottery that endures fire and gains eternity."
[Ceramic artist Seol Young Won's first solo exhibition in ten years.]

150
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:57,080
Who are those people next to Eun Tae Hee?

151
00:11:57,080 --> 00:11:58,270
That's Tae Hee's mom.

152
00:11:58,270 --> 00:12:00,610
They look alike, right?

153
00:12:00,610 --> 00:12:02,430
Who is it?

154
00:12:03,290 --> 00:12:05,790
Eun Tae Hee's mom.

155
00:12:13,930 --> 00:12:17,470
This used to be a traditional tea house.

156
00:12:25,430 --> 00:12:28,380
There really isn't anything that hasn't changed if we look corner by corner.

157
00:12:28,380 --> 00:12:32,610
I haven't changed, though. Bbuing bbuing.
(T/N: something aegyo say).

158
00:12:32,610 --> 00:12:37,750
That's right, your bad aegyo and tiny alcohol tolerance are the same.

159
00:12:38,900 --> 00:12:42,460
The thing that hasn't changed the most is my heart.

160
00:12:43,850 --> 00:12:48,930
The future is what's important. You're not going to change?

161
00:12:48,930 --> 00:12:50,580
No.

162
00:12:51,670 --> 00:12:53,660
Let's not separate.

163
00:12:53,660 --> 00:12:58,610
And don't ruin things. Got it, Seol Young Won?

164
00:13:01,860 --> 00:13:03,980
Of course.

165
00:13:17,330 --> 00:13:21,790
Soo Ji. Let's go home, you'll get a cold.

166
00:13:21,790 --> 00:13:26,280
Let's go home! If I get a cold, I can't grill the meat.

167
00:13:30,250 --> 00:13:32,760
[Mrs. Myeong]

168
00:13:32,760 --> 00:13:33,520
Yeah?

169
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:38,560
Where are you, my daughter? Why aren't you coming home or picking up your phone?

170
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:40,770
I'm coming.

171
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:45,560
She's acting so happy. How annoying.

172
00:13:53,570 --> 00:13:55,300
Let's go.

173
00:13:58,780 --> 00:14:02,460
I saw a boy in his twenties who was painting.

174
00:14:02,460 --> 00:14:05,470
I was really sad at the time.

175
00:14:05,470 --> 00:14:09,180
But, after I saw him painting... How should I say this?

176
00:14:09,180 --> 00:14:12,160
I felt like I was being comforted.

177
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:15,310
He looked like the happiest person in the world.

178
00:14:15,310 --> 00:14:17,360
Really?

179
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:23,560
After being so in love with you and not fearing anything, when I was working hard and making pottery,

180
00:14:23,560 --> 00:14:26,300
I probably looked like that, too.

181
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:31,300
Seol Young Won. Don't go home today.

182
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:34,610
What would we do?

183
00:14:34,610 --> 00:14:35,710
Don't go.

184
00:14:35,710 --> 00:14:37,120
Geum Shil would faint.

185
